Rakuen's Covenant Council has considered the dispatch registrar's spirit clearance report and issued a reckoning order targeting three hostile forces the Ventspeaker refugees identify as the actual enforcement layer preventing return: ash cult fire-keepers maintaining ritual fire-pits that function as territorial seal-markers, ash cult doctrinal enforcers who have converted the approach into an active patrol zone, and the western fold approach basilisk whose territory overlaps the only viable return corridor. All three must be removed before a formal return assessment can proceed.
Rakuen's Covenant Council has accepted the reckoning report and moved the Western Fold Approach to active return assessment status. The fire-pits are extinguished, the patrol zone has fragmented, and the basilisk's territory no longer blocks the corridor. The Council notes with measured caution that the deeper forces in the Western Fold remain entirely intact — the reckoning order was never meant to address the mountain itself, only the institutional apparatus that had settled over it like silt.
